AI.description: The AI competitors will add logic to this AI so its functions return valid and smart values.

runTurn.description: This is called every time it is this AI.player's turn.

returns.description: Represents if you want to end your turn. True means end your turn, False means to keep your turn going and re-call this function.

catEnergyMult.description: The multiplier for the amount of energy regenerated when resting in a shelter with the cat overlord.

currentPlayer.description: The player whose turn it is currently. That player can send commands. Other players cannot.

currentTurn.description: The current turn number, starting at 0 for the first player's turn.

gameObjects.description: A mapping of every game object's ID to the actual game object. Primarily used by the server and client to easily refer to the game objects via ID.

harvestCooldown.description: The amount of turns it takes for a Tile that was just harvested to grow food again.

jobs.description: All the Jobs that Units can have in the game.

mapHeight.description: The number of Tiles in the map along the y (vertical) axis.

mapWidth.description: The number of Tiles in the map along the x (horizontal) axis.

maxTurns.description: The maximum number of turns before the game will automatically end.

players.description: List of all the players in the game.

session.description: A unique identifier for the game instance that is being played.

starvingEnergyMult.description: The multiplier for the amount of energy regenerated when resting while starving.

tiles.description: All the tiles in the map, stored in Row-major order. Use `x + y * mapWidth` to access the correct index.

Game.description: Convert as many humans to as you can to survive in this post-apocalyptic wasteland.
Game.name: Catastrophe

gameObjectName.description: String representing the top level Class that this game object is an instance of. Used for reflection to create new instances on clients, but exposed for convenience should AIs want this data.

id.description: A unique id for each instance of a GameObject or a sub class. Used for client and server communication. Should never change value after being set.

logs.description: Any strings logged will be stored here. Intended for debugging.

GameObject.description: An object in the game. The most basic class that all game classes should inherit from automatically.

arguments.description: A string to add to this GameObject's log. Intended for debugging.
arguments.name: message

log.description: Adds a message to this GameObject's logs. Intended for your own debugging purposes, as strings stored here are saved in the gamelog.

actionCost.description: The amount of energy this Job normally uses to perform its actions.

carryLimit.description: How many combined resources a Unit with this Job can hold at once.

moves.description: The number of moves this Job can make per turn.

regenRate.description: The amount of energy normally regenerated when resting at a shelter.

upkeep.description: The amount of food per turn this Unit consumes. If there isn't enough food for every Unit, all Units become starved and do not consume food.

cat.description: The overlord cat Unit owned by this Player.

clientType.description: What type of client this is, e.g. 'Python', 'JavaScript', or some other language. For potential data mining purposes.

food.description: The amount of food owned by this player.

lost.description: If the player lost the game or not.

opponent.description: This player's opponent in the game.

reasonLost.description: The reason why the player lost the game.

reasonWon.description: The reason why the player won the game.

structures.description: Every Structure owned by this Player.

timeRemaining.description: The amount of time (in ns) remaining for this AI to send commands.

units.description: Every Unit owned by this Player.

upkeep.description: The total upkeep of every Unit owned by this Player. If there isn't enough food for every Unit, all Units become starved and do not consume food.

won.description: If the player won the game or not.

Player.description: A player in this game. Every AI controls one player.

effectRadius.description: The range of this Structure's effect. For example, a radius of 1 means this Structure affects a 3x3 square centered on this Structure.

materials.description: The number of materials in this Structure. Once this number reaches 0, this Structure is destroyed.

owner.description: The owner of this Structure if any, otherwise null.

tile.description: The Tile this Structure is on.

type.description: The type of Structure this is ('shelter', 'monument', 'wall', 'road', 'neutral').

food.description: The number of food dropped on this Tile.

harvestRate.description: The amount of food that can be harvested from this Tile per turn.

materials.description: The number of materials dropped on this Tile.

structure.description: The Structure on this Tile if present, otherwise null.

tileEast.description: The Tile to the 'East' of this one (x+1, y). Null if out of bounds of the map.

tileNorth.description: The Tile to the 'North' of this one (x, y-1). Null if out of bounds of the map.

tileSouth.description: The Tile to the 'South' of this one (x, y+1). Null if out of bounds of the map.

tileWest.description: The Tile to the 'West' of this one (x-1, y). Null if out of bounds of the map.

turnsToHarvest.description: The amount of turns before this resource can be harvested.

unit.description: The Unit on this Tile if present, otherwise null.

x.description: The x (horizontal) position of this Tile.

y.description: The y (vertical) position of this Tile.

Tile.description: A Tile in the game that makes up the 2D map grid.

gameObjectName.description: String representing the top level Class that this game object is an instance of. Used for reflection to create new instances on clients, but exposed for convenience should AIs want this data.

id.description: A unique id for each instance of a GameObject or a sub class. Used for client and server communication. Should never change value after being set.

logs.description: Any strings logged will be stored here. Intended for debugging.

arguments.description: A string to add to this GameObject's log. Intended for debugging.
arguments.name: message

log.description: Adds a message to this GameObject's logs. Intended for your own debugging purposes, as strings stored here are saved in the gamelog.

acted.description: Whether this Unit has performed its action this turn.

energy.description: The amount of energy this Unit has (from 0.0 to 100.0).

food.description: The amount of food this Unit is holding.

job.description: The Job this Unit was recruited to do.

materials.description: The amount of materials this Unit is holding.

movementTarget.description: The tile this Unit is moving to. This only applies to neutral fresh humans spawned on the road. Otherwise, the tile this Unit is on.

moves.description: How many moves this Unit has left this turn.

owner.description: The Player that owns and can control this Unit, or null if the Unit is neutral.

squad.description: The Units in the same squad as this Unit. Units in the same squad attack and defend together.

starving.description: Whether this Unit is starving. Starving Units regenerate energy at half the rate they normally would while resting.

tile.description: The Tile this Unit is on.

turnsToDie.description: The number of turns before this Unit dies. This only applies to neutral fresh humans created from combat. Otherwise, 0.

arguments.description: The Tile to attack.
arguments.name: tile

attack.description: Attacks an adjacent Tile. Costs an action for each Unit in this Unit's squad. Units in the squad without an action don't participate in combat. Units in combat cannot move afterwards.

returns.description: True if successfully attacked, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The name of the Job to change to.
arguments.name: job

changeJob.description: Changes this Unit's Job. Must be at max energy (100.0) to change Jobs.

returns.description: True if successfully changed Jobs, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The Tile to construct the Structure on. It must have enough materials on it for a Structure to be constructed.
arguments.name: tile

arguments.description: The type of Structure to construct on that Tile.
arguments.name: type

construct.description: Constructs a Structure on an adjacent Tile.

returns.description: True if successfully constructed a structure, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The Tile with the Unit to convert.
arguments.name: tile

convert.description: Converts an adjacent Unit to your side.

returns.description: True if successfully converted, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The Tile to deconstruct. It must have a Structure on it.
arguments.name: tile

deconstruct.description: Removes materials from an adjacent Tile's Structure. Soldiers do not gain materials from doing this, but can deconstruct friendly Structures as well.

returns.description: True if successfully deconstructed, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The Tile to drop materials/food on.
arguments.name: tile

arguments.description: The type of resource to drop ('material' or 'food').
arguments.name: resource

arguments.description: The amount of the resource to drop. Amounts <= 0 will drop as much as possible.
arguments.name: amount

drop.description: Drops some of the given resource on or adjacent to the Unit's Tile. Does not count as an action.

returns.description: True if successfully dropped the resource, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The Tile you want to harvest.
arguments.name: tile

harvest.description: Harvests the food on an adjacent Tile.

returns.description: True if successfully harvested, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The Tile this Unit should move to.
arguments.name: tile

move.description: Moves this Unit from its current Tile to an adjacent Tile.

returns.description: True if it moved, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The Tile to pickup materials/food from.
arguments.name: tile

arguments.description: The type of resource to pickup ('material' or 'food').
arguments.name: resource

arguments.description: The amount of the resource to pickup. Amounts <= 0 will pickup as much as possible.
arguments.name: amount

pickup.description: Picks up some materials or food on or adjacent to the Unit's Tile. Does not count as an action.

returns.description: True if successfully picked up a resource, false otherwise.

rest.description: Regenerates energy. Must be in range of a friendly shelter to rest. Costs an action. Units cannot move after resting.

returns.description: True if successfully rested, false otherwise.
